= content_for(:page_title) do
  LLMs

.max-w-prose
  = doc_info(url: "/llms-v#{LocoMotion::VERSION}.txt", image_path: "logos/openai.svg", image_alt: "OpenAI Logo") do
    :markdown
      **LocoMotion** provides a dedicated documentation file for Large Language
      Models (LLMs) to help you build faster with AI assistants!

.prose
  :markdown
    # LLM Documentation

    We generate a comprehensive text-based documentation file that is optimized
    for consumption by LLMs like ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini. This allows you
    to easily provide context about the LocoMotion component library to your
    AI assistant.

    ## Usage

    You can provide the documentation to your LLM in a few ways:

- # The three ways in, as one card row.
%div{ class: "mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3" }
  = daisy_card(css: "border border-base-300 bg-base-100") do
    %span{ class: "text-2xl" } 🔗
    %span{ class: "font-bold" } Direct link
    %p{ class: "text-sm text-base-content/70" }
      AI-powered editors like Cursor and Windsurf can add a documentation
      source by URL.
    %code{ class: "rounded-box bg-base-200 p-2 text-xs break-all" }
      = "#{request.base_url}/llms-v#{LocoMotion::VERSION}.txt"

  = daisy_card(css: "border border-base-300 bg-base-100") do
    %span{ class: "text-2xl" } 📡
    %span{ class: "font-bold" } llms.txt standard
    %p{ class: "text-sm text-base-content/70" }
      Tools that speak the llms.txt standard discover these automatically —
      an index and a full version.
    %code{ class: "rounded-box bg-base-200 p-2 text-xs break-all" }
      = "#{request.base_url}/llms.txt"
    %code{ class: "mt-1 rounded-box bg-base-200 p-2 text-xs break-all" }
      = "#{request.base_url}/llms-full.txt"

  = daisy_card(css: "border border-base-300 bg-base-100") do
    %span{ class: "text-2xl" } ⬇️
    %span{ class: "font-bold" } Manual upload
    %p{ class: "text-sm text-base-content/70" }
      Download the full documentation file and upload it directly to your
      chat session.
    %div{ class: "mt-1" }
      = daisy_button("Download llms-full.txt", icon: "arrow-down-tray", css: "btn-primary btn-sm", href: "/llms-full-v#{LocoMotion::VERSION}.txt", html: { download: true })

.max-w-prose
  = doc_note(css: "mt-8", modifier: :tip, title: "Pro Tip") do
    :markdown
      When asking your LLM to generate code, try prompting it with:

    = doc_code(language: "text", css: "my-4") do
      Using the LocoMotion component library at #{request.base_url}, create a...

    :markdown
      This helps the model understand which context to prioritize.

= daisy_divider

= doc_buttons(css: "mt-8", current_id: params[:id], section: "docs")
